articles.title: MOUSEOVER ELEMENT
articles.description: You’ll see how JavaScript functions work and practice your JavaScript logic

articles.title: CLOCK
articles.description: You get hands-on with the kind of actual work you’ll be doing as a JavaScript developer

articles.title: MAGIC 8 BALL
articles.description: It gives you a solid foundation for how to use Math.random to produce randomized results for JavaScript projects

articles.title: BUILD A TO-DO LIST
articles.description: You’ll beef up your skills at coding interactive lists, which lets users add, remove, and group items

articles.title: EPIC MIX PLAYLIST
articles.description: It helps you practice core JavaScript skills, such as forEach loops and event listeners, and work with functions and lists

articles.title: PET RESCUE
articles.description: It gives you a solid foundation for understanding factory function patterns and parameters

articles.title: DRUM KIT
articles.description: You can see the interaction between seeing elements on the page and listening to sound and learning how to add and remove elements

articles.title: SPEECH DETECTION
articles.description: It gives you a basis for understanding how speech detection works, which is good (and very cool!) to know

articles.title: STICKY NAVIGATION
articles.description: It teaches you how to keep your elements in a fixed position on a page, which is a skill you might need in your front end developer role

articles.title: GEOLOCATION
articles.description: You can learn more about how to develop for mobile, how geolocation works, and how to test your code using simulators or a different device
